1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:02,210
Greetings everyone.

2
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:10,210
Today we'll look at a quite well-known and interesting circuit called Kacher.

3
00:00:12,370 --> 00:00:26,890
This circuit is an autogenerator built on one transistor with feedback that goes directly from the cold end of the high-voltage coil to the base of this transistor.

4
00:00:27,530 --> 00:00:29,250
Why do we need this circuit?

5
00:00:29,910 --> 00:00:41,110
This circuit will help us answer the question of what frequency to tune the Tesla coil at relative to our resonator in the grenade.

6
00:00:43,130 --> 00:00:45,930
This question is often asked by subscribers.

7
00:00:47,170 --> 00:00:51,250
So, we'll assemble this circuit on this transistor.

8
00:00:51,330 --> 00:00:52,830
Think everyone has it.

9
00:00:53,870 --> 00:00:54,490
2SC5200.

10
00:00:56,550 --> 00:01:01,450
Basically we'll take it, since it's widespread and can be bought.

11
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:06,330
And look at this system's operation.

12
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:12,670
What we know and what's still unknown about how to tune these systems.

13
00:01:13,590 --> 00:01:14,910
Starting our circuit.

14
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:20,490
Power input we have plus-minus DC power source.

15
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:27,410
And power reaches immediately the first filtering capacitor.

16
00:01:29,490 --> 00:01:33,110
Capacitor is 100 nF, 275 V.

17
00:01:33,470 --> 00:01:37,950
Next reaches the mains filter with counter windings.

18
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:44,970
It's specifically made for DC voltage to pass through the mains filtering capacitance.

19
00:01:44,970 --> 00:01:49,890
Unimpeded, any variable component is suppressed.

20
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:55,950
After, power output reaches one more filtering capacitance.

21
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,870
Also 100 nF, 275 V.

22
00:02:00,110 --> 00:02:05,970
And then power reaches the main accumulator.

23
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:07,910
Electrolytic capacitor.

24
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,510
Its capacitance 47 µF at 400 V.

25
00:02:12,050 --> 00:02:27,410
Voltage here should be taken on this capacitor no less than 400 V, because in the whole system already there may be high-voltage potential, so this capacitor doesn't blow, isn't

26
00:02:27,410 --> 00:02:29,590
broken from high-voltage pickup.

27
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:37,990
Then in parallel with it a capacitor is installed, which also has special requirements.

28
00:02:38,370 --> 00:02:40,150
Also no less than 400 V.

29
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:44,090
Capacitance in this case 155 nF.

30
00:02:45,970 --> 00:02:47,990
But requirements are these.

31
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:52,290
Must be film capacitor, high-frequency.

32
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:55,450
CBB81 mark fits.

33
00:02:56,770 --> 00:03:07,670
It's needed for forming a sharp pulse that'll be on the collector of this transistor.

34
00:03:09,090 --> 00:03:15,090
This pulse is sent subsequently to the inductor of the Tesla high-voltage coil.

35
00:03:17,050 --> 00:03:29,530
System is assembled on a transistor and two resistors that form a voltage divider.

36
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:40,870
One resistor connects directly between minus power and transistor base, second resistor between plus power and transistor base.

37
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:49,090
A voltage divider is formed that creates an offset point on this transistor's base.

38
00:03:49,850 --> 00:04:04,450
But what needs to not be forgotten here is that not only two resistors work, but also a resistor formed by the base-emitter junction in the transistor's semiconductor itself.

39
00:04:05,670 --> 00:04:09,410
Such complex divider relative to minus we get.

40
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:12,250
Three resistances participate.

41
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:19,670
In this case resistance between base and emitter is 2.7 kΩ.

42
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:26,710
Resistance included between plus power and base is 3.3 kΩ.

43
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:32,350
Tested, works at resistance 1-10 kΩ.

44
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:44,430
The higher the value of this resistance, the less the whole system as a whole will consume.

45
00:04:45,030 --> 00:04:47,470
What interesting work.

46
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:51,970
This will be considered later, for now just explaining.

47
00:04:52,570 --> 00:04:57,570
Here by oscillogram we should get this signal.

48
00:04:58,530 --> 00:05:08,530
Width of this signal corresponds to half period of high-voltage coil oscillation.

49
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:15,630
And inside this signal should be as many high-frequency peaks as possible.

50
00:05:16,430 --> 00:05:29,070
They practically descend to zero of supply by voltage scale width.

51
00:05:29,990 --> 00:05:33,670
But slightly not all the way.

52
00:05:33,870 --> 00:05:44,190
And this forms such moment that the system ramps up with high-voltage high-frequency pulses.

53
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:49,870
But overall the high-voltage coil perceives this as one pulse.

54
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:56,110
And the more peaks here, the better this system's ramp-up happens.

55
00:05:58,230 --> 00:06:15,790
Also, if this system is used directly on installation, one of moments how to synchronize it simply, here schematically presented our pot core, the system deflecting from the TV

56
00:06:15,790 --> 00:06:16,470
screen.

57
00:06:17,830 --> 00:06:28,410
Here 28 turns, say, whoever fits how much on half, we put on this output or this fast-acting diode.

58
00:06:29,710 --> 00:06:43,590
This way we cut off the half from such signal, pass half-period of this signal and send to power input.

59
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:49,830
Exactly this capacitor will block this high-voltage spike.

60
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:59,770
Well as high-voltage, may be from 100 to 350-400 volts.

61
00:06:59,870 --> 00:07:03,350
That is when system absorbs, it doesn't rise higher.

62
00:07:03,350 --> 00:07:06,290
Also some drop happens on the diode.

63
00:07:07,590 --> 00:07:15,510
And main part, what this filter is for — it removes all error.

64
00:07:16,130 --> 00:07:25,830
And power reaching the system is already single-polar, synchronously with one half-period of push-pull.

65
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:38,890
When it works, we need, for example, to switch the diode either here or here, swap these wires, and can run this system on half-period positive or, say, by half-period

66
00:07:38,890 --> 00:07:39,610
negative.

67
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:41,290
Simplest synchronization.

68
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:43,470
Of course not the most efficient.

69
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:52,030
Much more efficient of course will be electronic synchronization, but nevertheless work with this synchronization is possible.

70
00:07:54,930 --> 00:08:08,290
Use of such filter of two capacitances and counter-wound transformer on a single core provides some decoupling from the power source.

71
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:18,910
And main thing, if we use this synchronization system, it removes interference present at input.

72
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:32,270
And it also filters interference that can come from Tesla high-voltage coil operation to power source back.

73
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:37,750
We also see we have grounding.

74
00:08:38,050 --> 00:08:42,030
It's connected directly to the emitter of this transistor.

75
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:51,550
And if we look, the minus goes through filter to grounding.

76
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:56,610
Also our grounding isn't directly connected.

77
00:08:56,830 --> 00:09:05,230
Galvanic connection exists, but connection by high-frequency part is absent.

78
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:15,430
This way we protect our common system from interference that may be during coil operation itself.

79
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,690
Here another interesting moment.

80
00:09:19,250 --> 00:09:24,750
This transistor has quite high parameters.

81
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:33,330
That is voltage between collector and base 230 volts max possible.

82
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:38,090
Voltage between collector and emitter 230 volts also.

83
00:09:38,590 --> 00:09:45,950
And voltage between emitter and base only 5 volts ultimate control possible.

84
00:09:47,110 --> 00:09:54,970
How does it work that we connect our transistor directly to cold end of high-voltage coil?

85
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:57,530
Seemingly kilovolts here.

86
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:03,330
Why ultimate voltage 5 volts, this transistor works?

87
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:13,990
The whole thing is during Tesla high-voltage coil operation we have phase shift between current and voltage.

88
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:22,130
And it turns out at this point, base-emitter junction, as such no high-voltage exists.

89
00:10:23,410 --> 00:10:38,190
There depending on mode may be tenths of volts, well or it all depends on offset point and coil ramp-up to 2-2.5 volts.

90
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:50,070
And need to understand, so our transistor doesn't fail, we created here with divider from resistors some offset, positive potential.

91
00:10:50,430 --> 00:11:02,270
And also our transistor starts, since it's NPN polarity, conductivity of this transistor, it triggers by positive half-period.

92
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:15,590
And need to watch so at this point on base voltage of offset plus voltage potential present in positive half-period don't exceed 5 volts.

93
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:19,570
After exceeding this transistor fails.

94
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:38,170
Works up to plus 150 degrees Celsius, and this means need to understand temperature, these 150 degrees Celsius, is temperature directly in semiconductor crystal.

95
00:11:38,570 --> 00:11:53,490
If we examine our transistor, semiconductor crystal is in this zone, mounted on this metal pad which is for us both pad for heat removal and it's

96
00:11:53,490 --> 00:11:58,650
galvanically connected directly with collector of this transistor.

97
00:11:59,530 --> 00:12:07,350
That is in this case 150 degrees is exactly crystal temperature, not heat sink.

98
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:23,370
Need to watch this transistor's heat sink temperature and approximately if our heat sink temperature rises to 120 degrees, we'll have danger that this transistor will fail

99
00:12:23,370 --> 00:12:32,630
since crystal temperature itself at 120 degrees of heat sink will already be in area 145 degrees inside transistor.

100
00:12:33,130 --> 00:12:41,910
Well and this circuit is designed so we won't have big temperature rises here.

101
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:51,670
At 24-volt power, I tested it also at 50 volts, heat sink handles great and basically no heating.

102
00:12:52,310 --> 00:13:07,610
We saw this system in some videos tunes so here's a single pulse, get maximum amplitude at this system's output.

103
00:13:08,110 --> 00:13:15,290
Want to say from practice it turned out this isn't the operating mode we need.

104
00:13:15,890 --> 00:13:33,330
Maximum output from coil at minimum consumption can only be at such pulse high-frequency operation of this transistor relative to high-voltage coil's frequency itself.

105
00:13:34,450 --> 00:13:40,630
Now we'll look at how system is implemented in metal.

106
00:13:42,210 --> 00:13:50,910
Before you the circuit layout on which all parts are mounted.

107
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:54,930
What do we see here first?

108
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:59,310
Power input terminals, plus and minus.

109
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:16,250
First filter capacitance 100 nF, filter itself with counter windings, after it second capacitance, main accumulator and main fast-acting reset capacitor.

110
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:20,390
From it there's plus output, here minus.

111
00:14:20,810 --> 00:14:25,470
From minus lead wire went directly to grounding.

112
00:14:26,790 --> 00:14:36,270
So assembled for fitting system of divider that creates offset on transistor base.

113
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:45,390
One transistor fits to plus, another connects to minus, directly to emitter.

114
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:46,870
This wire goes to base.

115
00:14:47,410 --> 00:14:54,190
Divider is selected for optimal operation, after which mounted on circuit.

116
00:14:55,070 --> 00:15:00,590
Transistor is on massive heat sink.

117
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:03,970
As it turned out, such big heat sink isn't needed.

118
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:12,690
This system, heat sink at 24-volt supply voltage doesn't heat above 45 degrees.

119
00:15:12,850 --> 00:15:14,410
Heat sink can be reduced.

120
00:15:15,010 --> 00:15:36,310
I didn't use thermal insulating pad, which is galvanic isolation between heat sink and transistor itself, in order that in system better cooling is organized.

121
00:15:37,550 --> 00:15:42,250
This system is heat sink-collector of this transistor.

122
00:15:42,430 --> 00:15:46,870
Can track oscillogram directly on it.

123
00:15:48,730 --> 00:15:54,570
Moving to, in my view, most important part of our system.

124
00:15:55,050 --> 00:15:57,710
This is our high-voltage coil.

125
00:16:00,110 --> 00:16:11,650
We often see in video clips from internet when these coils are wound on tubes taken from sewage, that is plastics.

126
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:19,390
As turned out in practice, plastic isn't suitable at all for winding these coils.

127
00:16:20,490 --> 00:16:21,490
What happens?

128
00:16:22,890 --> 00:16:25,350
Such experiment was set up.

129
00:16:26,050 --> 00:16:48,350
On this carcass, which is cardboard, can easily get baking foil, and there are very good, quality-made carcasses there.

130
00:16:48,970 --> 00:16:49,890
One of methods.

131
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:54,090
Or any other cardboard tubes you can find.

132
00:16:54,970 --> 00:17:05,790
On this carcass winding was done over length 30 cm, wire cross-section 0.75 mm.

133
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:17,490
And this coil was connected to such quite large in dimensions antenna.

134
00:17:17,990 --> 00:17:26,730
Antenna is made of aluminum wire, 7 turns, winding diameter 135 mm.

135
00:17:27,910 --> 00:17:42,030
Expected, by analogy with windings on plastic tubes, to see frequency in area 600 to 750 kHz.

136
00:17:42,190 --> 00:17:56,530
When system was started and frequency characteristic was taken, turned out for such long winding frequency together of whole system was 1.2 MHz.

137
00:17:57,530 --> 00:18:15,610
After which on carcass of equivalent diameter from plastic, like sewage tube, this same wire was wound and frequency characteristic was compared.

138
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:28,030
And turned out to achieve on this same system frequency 1.2 MHz, we needed to wind 9.5 mm on plastic tube.

139
00:18:29,070 --> 00:18:33,670
From which conclusion was made that plastic isn't suitable at all for these windings.

140
00:18:34,890 --> 00:18:38,770
Another negative feature of plastic tubes turns out.

141
00:18:38,950 --> 00:18:43,790
It very strongly suppresses both system frequency and its Q-factor.

142
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:48,050
High-voltage coil works much worse.

143
00:18:48,650 --> 00:18:57,810
Need to apply greater supply voltage for ramping up high-voltage Tesla coil specifically on plastic tube.

144
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:12,450
We'll see this system that's assembled like this can already be operational from 1.6 V applied voltage at system power input.

145
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:31,790
Already autogenerator starts and we have on... if we lay probe near this antenna, we'll see that clean nice sine already exists even at this supply voltage.

146
00:19:31,990 --> 00:19:35,230
That is the Q-factor of the system comes out very high.

147
00:19:36,410 --> 00:19:40,290
Now another interesting question often asked.

148
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:47,010
Can you wind these coils by soldering the wire?

149
00:19:47,870 --> 00:19:55,890
Here on this coil can see 1, 2, 3, 4 and on this side one more, fifth solder.

150
00:19:56,650 --> 00:20:03,330
During frequency fitting I used wire unwinding method.

151
00:20:04,390 --> 00:20:14,070
During this wire naturally had to be cut and for retuning to other frequencies wire was soldered.

152
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:30,350
As turned out, if you have good grounding in this case, here it's very good, welding cable 25 sq, but I tried also on 4 sq mm wire.

153
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:40,070
Special difference I didn't see particularly, so don't need to chase welding cable for improving these systems.

154
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:41,870
But nevertheless, good grounding.

155
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:59,930
And if grounding is good, good contact with soil, then deterioration of operation or any harmonics, distortion of sine signal and other things on wire that's soldered isn't observed.

156
00:21:00,090 --> 00:21:01,710
That is coil works cleanly.

157
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:15,130
Main thing to do is clean both wires of lacquer qualitatively, directly twist them between each other and only after this tin with solder.

158
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:20,850
Then heat-shrink is put on and this wire works without problems.

159
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:28,710
Now another important moment.

160
00:21:30,770 --> 00:21:45,390
Few know that Tesla coils work, if you can put it this way, perceive electromagnetic radiation from inductor by volume.

161
00:21:46,070 --> 00:21:56,270
That is for these inductor dimensions there are minimum allowable geometric dimensions of Tesla coil itself.

162
00:21:56,970 --> 00:22:12,990
In case these minimum dimensions aren't maintained, system inductor will already enter excitation, its own oscillations will form on it, it'll interfere with whole system operation and

163
00:22:12,990 --> 00:22:19,670
high-voltage coil will already be much worse coordinated with the inductor itself.

164
00:22:20,310 --> 00:22:33,690
Don't, for purposes of reducing frequency, wind with very thin wire, that is use wires less than 0.5 mm cross-section.

165
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:42,470
These Tesla coils on tubes diameter from 40 to 50 mm aren't advisable to make with thin wires.

166
00:22:42,990 --> 00:22:54,230
We need some volume occupied by this coil in space to perceive electromagnetic wave from this inductor.

167
00:22:55,630 --> 00:22:58,490
Need to understand this and coordinate.

168
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:03,050
Also there are two variants of frequency fitting.

169
00:23:03,890 --> 00:23:12,130
First we discussed, when we unwind wire, that way with unwinding wire we'll increase frequency.

170
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:15,810
Either we can go another direction.

171
00:23:16,170 --> 00:23:35,210
We can leave wire length in system, that which filled this carcass, and change frequency directly with help of geometric dimensions, say stretching, increasing diameter or increasing

172
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:37,650
turn count of antenna itself.

173
00:23:38,410 --> 00:23:43,010
In some cases in these systems we work with, it's advisable.

174
00:23:43,090 --> 00:23:58,810
Say, if we consider moment that need to leave certain length of high-voltage coil wire that correlates with receiving coil wire length, and frequency needs to be

175
00:23:58,810 --> 00:24:01,650
changed, that is fit by frequency.

176
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:09,670
Wire length stays unchanged, and frequency we change exactly with help of our antenna.

177
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:14,450
About the antenna, very important information.

178
00:24:16,810 --> 00:24:20,810
Antenna can't be wound with copper wire.

179
00:24:21,610 --> 00:24:30,370
First thing that happens, copper wire very hard parts with static.

180
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:45,390
It more, our material is intended for working exactly with direct current movement, that is heavy charge movement directly along surface or in crystal lattice of this

181
00:24:45,390 --> 00:24:46,510
conductor.

182
00:24:47,130 --> 00:24:52,310
This material is good to use where you need to create magnetic field.

183
00:24:52,870 --> 00:25:00,110
Where work with static is needed, recommend using exactly aluminum.

184
00:25:00,550 --> 00:25:03,370
First, such a test was conducted.

185
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:12,910
Wound antenna of aluminum and wound with same cross-section was antenna of copper wire.

186
00:25:13,370 --> 00:25:19,630
Dimensions, wire length, diameter were identical and frequency measurements were done.

187
00:25:20,030 --> 00:25:34,030
And turned out that with copper antenna system frequency was 150 kHz lower than with antenna of equivalent geometric dimensions of aluminum.

188
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:38,350
Can conduct these experiments and confirm yourself.

189
00:25:39,270 --> 00:25:42,470
That is, I don't recommend using copper for antenna.

190
00:25:43,170 --> 00:25:48,110
Copper creates, by the way, strong magnetic field.

191
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:57,610
When our systems work, we can't have magnetic field here in this zone right on the antenna.

192
00:25:58,090 --> 00:26:09,750
We need exactly alternating electric potential that'll act later, interact with magnetic field in our resonator.

193
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:12,730
That's why use aluminum.

194
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:18,150
Moving to our device's operation.

195
00:26:18,290 --> 00:26:21,570
Now look at power oscillograms.

196
00:26:23,590 --> 00:26:28,390
Will start this system from lab power source.

197
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:36,490
Now see voltage supply is 1.3 V and consumption is zero.

198
00:26:36,630 --> 00:26:38,830
That is system isn't started yet.

199
00:26:40,930 --> 00:26:47,790
Connected yellow oscilloscope channel, probe itself to collector of this transistor.

200
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:57,890
Oscilloscope common connected to grounding wire, actually to transistor's emitter and wire going to ground.

201
00:26:59,890 --> 00:27:09,850
Now I'll smoothly raise supply voltage and we'll see voltage at which system starts.

202
00:27:10,210 --> 00:27:18,530
That is we'll see on blue oscilloscope channel oscillations of sine form.

203
00:27:20,170 --> 00:27:21,390
Raising voltage.

204
00:27:22,970 --> 00:27:32,890
And here we see voltage was raised by just some tenths of volt.

205
00:27:33,150 --> 00:27:37,850
Now it's 1.3 V.

206
00:27:37,950 --> 00:27:42,610
And see practically no consumption from system at all.

207
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:46,070
But system already works.

208
00:27:47,990 --> 00:27:55,470
That is, wound on cardboard carcass provides very high system Q-factor.

209
00:27:55,570 --> 00:27:59,950
It can work with minimum consumption.

210
00:28:02,130 --> 00:28:04,190
Raising consumption.

211
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:06,890
Now steadily visible.

212
00:28:07,170 --> 00:28:09,210
1.4 V.

213
00:28:09,970 --> 00:28:11,330
1.5 V.

214
00:28:11,330 --> 00:28:13,610
1.6 V.

215
00:28:13,630 --> 00:28:14,670
1.7 V.

216
00:28:14,670 --> 00:28:16,550
1.8 V.

217
00:28:17,250 --> 00:28:35,270
At such 1.8 V consumption, 0.03 A, on the antenna we already have some potential that can be fixed with neon bulb.

218
00:28:36,170 --> 00:28:38,870
See lamp glows when touching wire.

219
00:28:40,090 --> 00:28:43,290
System starts showing our properties.

220
00:28:44,050 --> 00:28:48,410
Of course at such values we don't exploit it.

