And we'll examine oscillogram of transistor operation directly on collector.

223
00:29:00,470 --> 00:29:14,460
So we see how system works, synchronize and examine.

224
00:29:14,900 --> 00:29:25,420
Here we see our peaks I talked about, high-frequency on collector.

225
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:37,220
See synchronization, transistor startup happens at positive half-period of coil oscillation itself.

226
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:51,260
Now system operating frequency, can see in upper right corner, 1.33 MHz.

227
00:29:52,780 --> 00:30:02,640
Winding now is on coil carcass 4.5 cm.

228
00:30:03,320 --> 00:30:08,140
Diameter of carcass itself is 25 cm winding.

229
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:15,400
At such antenna visible frequency quite high.

230
00:30:16,420 --> 00:30:21,800
And see our transistor starts working.

231
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:31,080
First spike, then voltage level drop, then another spike and another.

232
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:34,100
Now I'll raise supply voltage too.

233
00:30:34,100 --> 00:30:36,260
Now it's 7.5 V.

234
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:40,300
And we'll see number of these spikes will increase.

235
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,420
But with this amplitude will grow.

236
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:46,020
Bring to nominal.

237
00:30:46,900 --> 00:30:48,020
Now 9 V.

238
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:57,020
And look at spike amplitude when supply is 24 V.

239
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:06,760
Now precisely set 24 V supply.

240
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:12,760
See another peak appeared.

241
00:31:13,860 --> 00:31:22,100
That is with raising specifically amplitude of supply voltage, number of such spikes will be higher.

242
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:31,560
And the more number of these spikes, the better our system works, more economically.

243
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:36,000
Than when we tune system to have only one peak.

244
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:42,760
In this case spike amplitude visible.

245
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:51,080
It's, highest amplitude by first pulse is 136 V.

246
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:54,260
At 24 V supply.

247
00:31:55,240 --> 00:32:03,920
And see voltage corresponds to 24 V applied to input.

248
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:11,000
And consumes just 0.6 A.

249
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:21,240
Also can note lamp that's near antenna burns.

250
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:25,380
Fluorescent burns brightly, very well.

251
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:32,840
That is all effects accompanying normal mode operation, we have.

252
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:37,600
Neon lamp glows at big distance.

253
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:39,540
Now look at distance.

254
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:45,620
Starts glowing somewhere from 35 cm to antenna itself.

255
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:54,900
Also there's stable discharge to metal objects.

256
00:32:56,680 --> 00:32:58,220
Now examining it.

257
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:10,020
It corresponds... Length about a centimeter.

258
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:17,840
Can stretch stable arc.

259
00:33:21,490 --> 00:33:26,570
That is all accompanying effects with such tuning system has.

260
00:33:27,670 --> 00:33:35,310
It works no worse than when we have only one spike, but in much more economical mode.

261
00:33:36,230 --> 00:33:39,050
Recommend exactly such operating mode on Kacher.

262
00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:40,730
You'll see difference.

263
00:33:42,330 --> 00:33:44,650
It's brightly noticeable.

264
00:33:48,190 --> 00:34:00,930
Also can verify interesting moment of operation if we synchronize oscilloscope not relative to grounding wire but relative to plus supply.

265
00:34:01,150 --> 00:34:03,710
Our grounding was now synchronization.

266
00:34:03,930 --> 00:34:11,430
Now we'll hang on plus supply and look what'll be on collector.

267
00:34:12,850 --> 00:34:24,190
Hooked common on plus, attached to heat sink, to eye, since it's galvanically not connected with collector.

268
00:34:26,370 --> 00:34:33,050
And now examining operation in such measurement.

269
00:34:37,650 --> 00:34:39,170
Raising voltage.

270
00:34:42,110 --> 00:34:49,310
Now 19, 20, 24 V supply.

271
00:34:50,850 --> 00:34:56,910
What's interesting to note in such mode?

272
00:34:56,990 --> 00:35:17,130
Since we now synchronize relative to plus supply, see our maximum amplitude is less, 106 V, but we can also see that drop amplitude in minus common, which

273
00:35:17,130 --> 00:35:24,230
goes, since synchronization by plus, it corresponds approximately to supply voltage.

274
00:35:25,170 --> 00:35:31,430
Now 24 V, but we fix here about 27 V drop.

275
00:35:31,550 --> 00:35:44,350
That is some shift to minus observed, but peaks are also positive even relative to plus supply of system.

276
00:35:47,190 --> 00:36:03,120
Nothing mysterious here, because spike amplitude itself has positive potential much greater than potential of supply applied to plus input.

277
00:36:03,380 --> 00:36:09,280
So relative to plus we see our drop, practically equal to supply voltage.

278
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:15,320
Well and pulse itself goes to positive half-period.

279
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:33,460
Here marker under number one, yellow, shows us moment of beginning of zero of scale, relative to which oscillogram is centered on screen.

280
00:36:36,630 --> 00:36:55,130
Can also, without fear of burning oscilloscope course, do measurements on transistor base when system is connected to grounding.

281
00:36:55,530 --> 00:37:01,190
Nothing scary, oscillogram can be observed there.

282
00:37:01,330 --> 00:37:15,090
Now I'll connect second oscilloscope probe directly to base and look at signal coming to us from coil to base of this transistor.

283
00:37:16,610 --> 00:37:21,790
Connected second oscilloscope channel directly to transistor base.

284
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:29,190
See it's at middle point of connection on resistor divider.

285
00:37:30,070 --> 00:37:34,090
That is connected here.

286
00:37:35,330 --> 00:37:40,390
Actually connected with cold end from high-voltage coil.

287
00:37:41,110 --> 00:37:54,970
Such measurements can be done with oscilloscope at this point provided you have good grounding of high-voltage coil.

288
00:37:56,470 --> 00:38:05,370
If you doubt your grounding, need to assemble here, look at something.

289
00:38:05,890 --> 00:38:09,830
Need device, oscilloscope itself, not be grounded.

290
00:38:10,910 --> 00:38:12,870
This is important for work.

291
00:38:13,610 --> 00:38:18,750
Also I recommend for device powering.

292
00:38:19,170 --> 00:38:25,090
They're usually quite expensive for us and we don't want to part with them.

293
00:38:25,650 --> 00:38:32,590
Need device power be decoupled from grounding.

294
00:38:33,490 --> 00:38:40,970
That is on device plug we can always see grounding contact.

295
00:38:41,310 --> 00:38:47,230
So it shouldn't be connected to grounding during work with high-voltage coil.

296
00:38:47,750 --> 00:38:48,110
That's one.

297
00:38:48,350 --> 00:38:49,130
And another.

298
00:38:50,210 --> 00:38:59,230
Oscilloscope devices, signal generators and so on better turn on, for example, through two transformers.

299
00:38:59,350 --> 00:39:12,050
Say if you have two transformers of about 200-300 watts power, sufficient for powering several devices.

300
00:39:12,230 --> 00:39:13,930
Well or at least for oscilloscope.

301
00:39:14,450 --> 00:39:22,530
You turn it on first with winding that goes for mains 220 V.

302
00:39:22,610 --> 00:39:28,010
After which in step-down mode it outputs say 12, 24 or 36 V.

303
00:39:28,650 --> 00:39:31,270
And second analogous connects in reverse.

304
00:39:32,050 --> 00:39:34,450
With say 12 V winding.

305
00:39:34,450 --> 00:39:44,210
From 12 V output of first capacitor already take output voltage that's applied to device's mains winding.

306
00:39:45,570 --> 00:39:50,770
This way you decouple device through two transformers from mains.

307
00:39:51,550 --> 00:39:54,870
This is very useful in work and will protect your devices.

308
00:39:55,510 --> 00:40:00,170
Well and oscillogram we can observe on transistor base.

309
00:40:00,830 --> 00:40:02,070
This is by voltage.

310
00:40:02,490 --> 00:40:03,470
Now oscillogram.

311
00:40:04,610 --> 00:40:14,270
See transistor on collector repeats voltage form on base.

312
00:40:15,950 --> 00:40:23,030
These signals we have, exactly in positive half-period.

313
00:40:23,970 --> 00:40:26,550
This is for interest.

314
00:40:26,610 --> 00:40:31,050
If interested, can look for yourself, investigate.

315
00:40:32,270 --> 00:40:41,190
And also we can do, say, measurement in this system through current sensor.

316
00:40:41,930 --> 00:40:50,930
Now we'll look made on ferrite ring what happens in grounding wire.

317
00:40:51,070 --> 00:40:54,250
Can examine exactly by current.

318
00:40:54,430 --> 00:40:57,150
Now I'll install sensor and look too.

319
00:40:59,590 --> 00:41:01,990
Connected current sensor.

320
00:41:02,430 --> 00:41:08,930
It's put directly on wire going to grounding from transistor emitter.

321
00:41:11,250 --> 00:41:19,710
And second oscilloscope channel is about 15 cm from antenna.

322
00:41:20,250 --> 00:41:23,310
By the way, another important note about device protection.

323
00:41:23,690 --> 00:41:36,570
Never connect oscilloscope to high-voltage end of coil, or its ending, which is this antenna.

324
00:41:37,650 --> 00:41:40,870
Can very easily part with your device.

325
00:41:40,970 --> 00:41:52,430
All voltage measurements in this case done with probe that's at some distance from high-voltage part.

326
00:41:53,450 --> 00:42:00,450
I use probes, recommend these for 1500 V.

327
00:42:00,710 --> 00:42:10,070
They very well transmit both frequencies and voltage even when working with ordinary electronics.

328
00:42:10,250 --> 00:42:15,270
That is specifically bought them, they don't come in oscilloscope kit.

329
00:42:15,570 --> 00:42:23,050
But nevertheless 1500 V you have good reserve so as not to burn device.

330
00:42:24,710 --> 00:42:28,250
And now we connected current sensor, examining oscillogram.

331
00:42:29,730 --> 00:42:37,370
Remind, yellow channel is current in grounding wire, blue is voltage.

332
00:42:37,950 --> 00:42:45,870
We see we have phase shift between current, yellow channel, and voltage.

333
00:42:46,270 --> 00:42:49,650
And see such characteristic signals by current.

334
00:42:49,870 --> 00:42:53,230
That is recall our this signal.

335
00:42:55,230 --> 00:43:01,110
These peak strikes, they're reflected for us exactly by current.

336
00:43:01,150 --> 00:43:04,030
These points above sine.

337
00:43:04,930 --> 00:43:15,350
And correct inclusion of current sensor for this system will be moment when current leads voltage.

338
00:43:15,430 --> 00:43:17,090
Voltage now blue channel.

339
00:43:17,090 --> 00:43:27,550
Now we don't precisely see 90-degree phase shift, because to precisely examine this, need to hang resistance on current sensor.

340
00:43:28,190 --> 00:43:41,450
But nevertheless, here 90-degree shift actually in our high-voltage coil, because all processes for us happen by current in systems.

341
00:43:42,410 --> 00:43:43,370
Why by current?

342
00:43:43,470 --> 00:43:55,730
Because to start, whole process starts when transistor commutates voltage applied to it, consequently current is fed to inductor.

343
00:43:56,330 --> 00:43:58,490
Inductor forms magnetic field.

344
00:43:59,030 --> 00:44:02,290
Magnetic field creates strike on coil.

345
00:44:02,430 --> 00:44:07,330
That is we understand current passed through inductor, created magnetic field.

346
00:44:07,490 --> 00:44:15,230
Magnetic field acts on this coil, after which oscillations ramp up in this coil.

347
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:19,510
So voltage lags relative to current for us.

348
00:44:21,110 --> 00:44:30,210
And correct inclusion of polarity will be exactly that moment when we examine oscillogram, exactly when current leads voltage.

349
00:44:33,330 --> 00:44:35,330
Good luck everyone in experiments.

350
00:44:35,510 --> 00:44:58,030
In subsequent videos we'll look at how this layout assembled will help us determine the frequency at which high-voltage, high-frequency part should work relative to our grenade.
